title: MORENO VALLEY: City boards being filled
text:
By IMRAN GHORI / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 22, 2015 1:50 p.m. MORENO VALLEY: City boards being filled Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Moreno Valley is seeking to fill vacancies on three advisory boards. , DAVID BAUMAN, FILE PHOTO Related article » Moreno Valley is looking to fill vacancies on varous city advisory boards.
One seat is open on the Senior Citizens’ Board and two seats each are open on the Recreational Trails Board and the Environmental and Historical Preservation Board.
Applicants must be Moreno Valley residents. The positions are unpaid.
Applications are available at moval.org or at the City Clerk’s office at 14177 Frederick Street. They are due by Friday, Nov. 13 at 4:30 p.m.
